reviewText: Makes me want to retire there. The geography, the climate, the history. Except for the ignorant voters, New England has it all.

reviewText: This item is listed as a 1:77 widescreen program which it is not!  It's in fact 1:33 fullscreen, a format that nobody wants anymore.  Perhaps the makers of this DVD purposely submitted the wrong information to Amazon to help generate some sales... If it works, why not?  Well, they certainly fooled me.  Like others, I certainly would have avoided this product had I known the truth.  One can tell by the picture distortions that it was a VHS camera used for all the fly-overs.  The true copyright is 1991, so this was taped over 20 years ago.  Fraudulent!

reviewText: After spending alot of time in New England sates on vacation it was fun to see the places visited from the air. We would watch and pik out the sights we visited. We also saw new places we plan to visit. The dvd was great to watch on rainy days and cold nights.

reviewText: If you can't get to New England, this is the next best thing. It covers all 6 New England States and the dvd is shot from a helicopter. The filming is absolutely beautiful. The music is also very nice. I give this dvd a A+++...highly recommend it. I have watched it over and over and it never gets boring.

reviewText: Quality of the video and accompanying music was excellent in all regards.  THE ONLY COMPLAINT THAT I HAVE IS THAT I WAS SPECIFICALLY LOOKING FOR BLURAY, and Amazon chose to mix this video in with the other blurays, so I chose to buy it, thinking (and my fault for not looking closer) that it was a Bluray also.  It was not.  But it is of good enough quality that I kept it anyway.
